If you're looking for a great burger in Kakaako/Ala Moana, then go to Chubbies Burgers! This is a food truck, so don't go expecting a sit-down restaurant. You can order to-go or you can eat there as they have outdoor open seating. Credit cards are accepted and they're open 10:30-9pm daily. I recommend the Ten Gallon burger (Bacon, BBQ sauce, cheddar cheese) or the El Rey (pepper jack, avacado, panko crusted onion rings, and ranch sauce). All burgers use local grass-fed beef and is served on a house made potato pun. There's also amazing fries to choose from too. Overall, you'll be glad you ate here. Just remember, for a couple bucks more you can get the "fancier" burgers and it's totally worth it!

McDonalds would cost $30 but for the extra $12, you get fresh avocados, golden crispy onion rings and a bunch of add ons for your burger.  Always a line but never waited longer than 10 minutes. You will never go back to a McDonald burger again!  The parking is horrible but I think it's cute how they ask if this will be a take out!  Lol!  It's a food truck! AND. No need for ketchup! You want to taste all that real flavor. Then you'll be hooked, just like me.

First off, Chubbies is a food truck. It’s delicious and I love myself a good food truck, but Google says it’s between Starbucks and Wahoo and the South Shore Market map (in the TJ Maxx/Pier 1/Nordstrom Rack area) says it’s over there with the other food places. But it’s in the parking lot of Starbucks and Wahoo if you’re looking for it. The burger El Ray (I think) was delicious. My new favorite burger and burger place! Sooooo good. The fries leave something to be desired, but the burger is amazing. I don’t like mayo/aioli and forgot to ask for the burger without but I ate the entire thing, mayo and all. So definitely worth checking out!! I’ll be back!
